    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.37b.10"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">10</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <hi rend="caps">THE ACADEMY OF AMERICAN POETS
                        
                    ∙ THE ACADEMY OF AMERICAN POETS ∙</hi> 
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>A Winged Horse</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <hi rend="caps">FOUNDED 1934
                    
                    1078 MADISON AVENUE NEW YORK, N Y 10028
                        <lb/>
                    YUKON</hi> 8-6783
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>August 27, 1973</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Skyrim Farm</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Route #7</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri 65201</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am very happy to be able to announce to you that the Board of Chancellors of The Academy of American Poets has, by special ballot with a majority vote, elected you an Honorary Fellow of the Academy.</p>
                
                <p>This recognition is based on the stipulation in the Academy's Charter that "poets of proven merit" may be so honored. Prompted by appreciation for your long years of service (from 1951 to 1967) to the Academy as a Chancellor, it is our pleasure to hold a very special salute to four of the Academy's Honora<del>ble</del><add>ry</add> Fellows during next Spring, and as part of the Academy's 40th Anniversary celebration.</p> 
                
                <p>We will advise you as to when and where this salute will be held, and hope to make it outstanding. I also very much hope that you can be present and participate.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Most sincerely yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Marie Bullock</signed>
                    <signed>Mrs. Hugh Bullock
                    President</signed> 
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <p>I do not want to delay this letter longer, as I am out of town, but the New York office has failed to include the names of the other Honorary Fellow<unclear>s.</unclear> They are: The Hon. Archibald MacLeish, a Fellow in 196<unclear/> and a former Chancellor; Robert Nathan, a Chancellor form 1951 to 1968; and John Hall Wheelock a Chancellor from 1947 to 1971, as well as a Voting Member and Director.</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
